
# -+---+- Conventional Commit Message Template -+---+-
# -+- Format -+-
# <type>([scope]): <description>
# 
# [optional body]
# 
# [optional footer(s)]
# 
# -+- SemVer -+-
# MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
# 
# -+- Types -+-
# fix       : A bug fix (SemVer: PATCH)
# feat      : A new feature (SemVer: MINOR)
# ci        : Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts (example scopes: Travis, Circle, BrowserStack, SauceLabs)
# style     : Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
# build     : Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies (example scopes: gulp, broccoli, npm)
# test      : Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
# perf      : A code change that improves performance
# refactor  : A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# chore     : Maintenance tasks
# docs      : Documentation only changes
# 
# 
# -+---+- Personal Commit Message Template -+---+-
# ini: Initial commit
# 
# add: Add new feature (or config)
# fix: Fix broken feature (or config)
# chg: Change a feature
# upd: Update a feature
# fmt: Reformat a file (manual or prettier)
# 
# mov: Moving a file or directory
# cop: Copy a file or directory
# rmv: Remove a features (single: file or directory)
# 
# cfg: Add/change a configuration files
# rwt: Rewrite a features (single: file or directory)
# 